name: Jimmy Butler
summary: Amidst a flurry of trade rumors, Jimmy Butler has reportedly expressed a preference for a trade out of Miami. Heat president Pat Riley has, however, stated that the team has no intention of trading the star forward. Butler's trade request comes amidst recent ankle and illness issues that have sidelined him from games. Despite these hurdles, the Heat remain committed to keeping Butler on the roster. The situation has raised questions about the team's chemistry and the possibility of a blockbuster trade involving Butler and potential landing spots such as the Phoenix Suns and Golden State Warriors. Riley's declaration that the Heat will not trade Butler suggests a hardening of the team's stance, but rumors persist due to Butler's reported desire for a change of scenery.

In particular, laptop deals are said to be better than those seen during Black Friday. Major retailers like The Good Guys and John Lewis in the UK, as well as Amazon and New Look, are participating in the sales event. Experts recommend taking advantage of the deals available during Boxing Day sales, and even advise grabbing them as soon as possible to secure the best bargains. summary: Geno Smith, the quarterback for the Seattle Seahawks, is currently dealing with a knee injury that has limited his mobility on the field. Despite the injury, Smith is expected to play in Week 16 against the Minnesota Vikings. Smith has been focused on preparing for the game and is not dwelling on past mistakes or his current performance. He has also spoken out about his future with the team, but there have been no recent updates. In a game against the Vikings, Smith threw a pair of interceptions, but his performance was overshadowed by a big play made by Dallas Turner, who came up with his first career NFL interception.

name: Jim Larranaga
summary: After two years since his team's Final Four run, Miami men's basketball coach Jim Larrañaga has resigned, citing exhaustion. Larrañaga, the university's all-time winningest head men's basketball coach, expressed his weariness with the business side of sports and the impact on his personal life. Assistant coach Bill Courtney will take over for the remainder of the season. This decision marks a significant departure for the Hurricanes, who have been led by Larrañaga since 2011 and experienced a significant resurgence under his leadership.

summary: The highly anticipated film adaptation of the Broadway musical "Wicked" is set to make its streaming debut on New Year's Eve 2024.
